WEBVTT

00:11.137 --> 00:13.013
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.013 --> 00:15.433
[Mickey] Back in Primm,
inside a casino there's

00:15.433 --> 00:17.060
a gorgeous green horseshoe

00:17.060 --> 00:18.477
filled with four million
in cash.

00:18.477 --> 00:20.105
No one's even watching it.

00:20.105 --> 00:22.398
Tomorrow night,
in the middle of the party,

00:22.398 --> 00:24.817
we cut the power,
we grab the horseshoe,

00:24.817 --> 00:26.402
and we're out
before anyone is the wiser.

00:26.402 --> 00:28.196
[tires squeal]

00:29.155 --> 00:30.698
Shit just went bad, that's all.

00:30.698 --> 00:32.242
Now we gotta get you hid.

00:32.242 --> 00:33.909
We will figure something out,
all right?

00:33.909 --> 00:35.744
Good-bye, beautiful.

00:35.744 --> 00:38.247
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

00:38.247 --> 00:39.957
I'll be in touch.

00:39.957 --> 00:41.750
Four million dollars
in that fucking horseshoe?

00:41.750 --> 00:43.086
Yeah.

00:43.086 --> 00:44.087
Other than the cops,

00:44.087 --> 00:45.212
who else is looking for it?

00:45.212 --> 00:47.339
Just a cocksucker
named Little Bill Primm.

00:47.339 --> 00:49.091
I'll pick you up
tomorrow morning.

00:49.091 --> 00:50.885
[Sylvie] Mickey?

00:50.885 --> 00:51.969
[Mickey] Yeah, it's me, babe.

00:51.969 --> 00:53.888
[tires squeal]

00:53.888 --> 00:55.055
[Sylvie] Where are you, baby?

00:55.055 --> 00:56.640
[Mickey] Our van went to shit.

00:56.640 --> 00:59.435
We're stranded on the side
of the road.

00:59.435 --> 01:01.812
Where?
I'll come get you.

01:01.812 --> 01:03.814
We're gonna act like
this never happened.

01:03.814 --> 01:05.108
[camera clicks]

01:05.108 --> 01:07.735
Unless you ever return to Primm.

01:07.735 --> 01:11.114
[Bunchy] Her brother Marco just
put her into a mental hospital.

01:11.114 --> 01:12.823
How could you do that to family?

01:12.823 --> 01:16.244
You're my wife, Teresa,
and Maria's mother,

01:16.244 --> 01:17.620
and we're fuckin' leavin'.

01:17.620 --> 01:19.205
[Ray] You want Belikov?
Give me one day.

01:19.205 --> 01:20.706
[Belikov grunts]

01:20.706 --> 01:22.124
♪♪♪

01:22.124 --> 01:24.127
[Ray] .45's got his fingerprints
on it.

01:24.127 --> 01:25.920
There's a duffle of guns
in the ceiling.

01:25.920 --> 01:28.131
Eight counts of homicide's
gonna stick a lot better

01:28.131 --> 01:29.256
than a trafficking charge.

01:29.256 --> 01:30.674
[Sonia]
I vouched for you

01:30.674 --> 01:32.635
with very powerful people
in Moscow

01:32.635 --> 01:34.720
who would have far preferred
to retaliate against you

01:34.720 --> 01:36.222
for framing Mr. Belikov.

01:36.222 --> 01:38.183
[Ray] Belikov's out.

01:38.183 --> 01:40.059
- [Ray] We're done.
- [Sonia] Go see him.

01:40.059 --> 01:42.145
Apologize for any problems
that you might have caused.

01:42.145 --> 01:44.480
[Belikov] You've been useful
for Sonia.

01:44.480 --> 01:46.482
Now be useful to me.

01:46.482 --> 01:48.318
We had a party.

01:48.318 --> 01:50.320
Party got bad.
She got excited,

01:50.320 --> 01:51.695
and she break her neck.

01:51.695 --> 01:53.239
Ship her back to my people
in Moscow.

01:53.239 --> 01:54.406
They will dispose.

01:54.406 --> 01:56.283
- Ah!
- Look at me!

01:56.283 --> 01:57.493
[gunshot]

01:57.493 --> 01:59.745
♪ dramatic music ♪

02:10.297 --> 02:13.300
[Dmitri muttering in Russian]

02:13.300 --> 02:16.345
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

02:16.345 --> 02:21.350
♪♪♪

02:44.331 --> 02:45.833
[footsteps approaching]

02:48.460 --> 02:51.463
[phone clicking]

02:54.174 --> 02:55.342
[phone chimes]

02:56.385 --> 02:58.345
[phone chimes and buzzes]

03:00.306 --> 03:02.016
[phone beeps]

03:03.350 --> 03:05.353
[gasps]

03:05.353 --> 03:06.395
[quietly]
Oh, my God.

03:06.395 --> 03:08.188
[phone rings]

03:08.188 --> 03:09.523
[gasps]

03:09.523 --> 03:11.817
[cell phone beeps]

03:11.817 --> 03:15.195
Hello?

03:15.195 --> 03:16.989
Dyadya?

03:16.989 --> 03:18.616
Did you see?

03:18.616 --> 03:20.200
[Sonia]
Yes.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.077
He arrived in Moscow yesterday.

03:22.077 --> 03:25.456
Why didn't you tell me
he was missing?

03:25.456 --> 03:27.375
I didn't know.

03:27.375 --> 03:29.752
I'll be at the gallery at 7:30.

03:29.752 --> 03:32.255
You meet me there
with Vlad and Waller.

03:32.255 --> 03:34.089
[Sonia]
Yes, 7:30.

03:34.089 --> 03:36.884
We'll be there.

03:36.884 --> 03:38.177
♪♪♪

03:38.177 --> 03:41.180
[phone clicking]

03:42.598 --> 03:44.808
Vlad, we have a problem.

03:44.808 --> 03:49.813
♪♪♪

03:55.278 --> 03:57.280
[police siren wails]

04:12.961 --> 04:14.463
[car door closes]

04:23.431 --> 04:25.891
What do you want, Barnes?

04:25.891 --> 04:27.518
Tell me something,
how is it that you manage

04:27.518 --> 04:29.144
to always get right
in the middle

04:29.144 --> 04:32.440
of every fucking thing, huh?

04:32.440 --> 04:34.108
Customs official
was found murdered

04:34.108 --> 04:36.402
at port this morning.

04:39.238 --> 04:41.490
I got nothin' to do with that.

04:43.325 --> 04:46.620
Russians got to you,
didn't they?

04:46.620 --> 04:48.622
I don't know what you're
talking about, Frank.

04:48.622 --> 04:50.458
Let's cut the bullshit, Ray.

04:50.458 --> 04:52.543
[Frank]
Word is Belikov is dead.

04:52.543 --> 04:55.338
In about a minute, you're gonna
come crawlin' to me for help.

04:55.338 --> 04:58.424
That is if you can still crawl.

04:58.424 --> 05:01.176
So if you got something to say,

05:01.176 --> 05:03.303
now's a good time.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.067
[phone rings]

05:17.067 --> 05:18.819
- [phone beeps]
- Yeah?

05:18.819 --> 05:20.487
[Ray] There was a murder
at the port this morning.

05:20.487 --> 05:22.114
Find out who it was.

05:22.114 --> 05:23.157
[Lena] All right,
what am I lookin' for?

05:23.157 --> 05:24.158
A fuckin' murder.

05:24.158 --> 05:25.159
Just do it, Lena.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.869
[Bluetooth beeps]

05:26.869 --> 05:29.288
- Thank you, Lena.
- [phone beeps]

05:29.288 --> 05:30.497
You're welcome, Ray.

05:34.168 --> 05:37.087
[Mickey] Looks like a little
cemetery of broken hearts.

05:37.087 --> 05:40.466
- Yeah.
- You've seen it all, I bet.

05:40.466 --> 05:41.508
Yeah.

05:41.508 --> 05:45.304
Angry wives, screaming wives,

05:45.304 --> 05:47.973
cheatin' wives,

05:47.973 --> 05:50.184
and husbands too, of course.

05:50.184 --> 05:52.394
You looking for something
in particular?

05:52.394 --> 05:54.354
True love, my friend.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.190
Like anybody.

05:56.190 --> 05:59.777
But small gestures won't do it

05:59.777 --> 06:02.029
for a man my age.

06:02.029 --> 06:04.114
Tell you what,
let me take a look at the .9 mil

06:04.114 --> 06:05.908
with the silencer.

06:12.164 --> 06:16.460
♪♪♪

06:17.795 --> 06:19.379
You don't want
to get rid of things.

06:19.379 --> 06:21.381
You want to get rid
of the feelings.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.300
Ah, you sound like Ezra.

06:23.300 --> 06:25.552
Ezra was a wise man.

06:25.552 --> 06:28.096
You forget.
I met him in shul.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.306
[quietly]
Yeah.

06:29.306 --> 06:32.309
[elevator door gears grinding]

06:33.477 --> 06:38.482
♪♪♪

06:47.616 --> 06:49.618
Get out.
I'll drive.

06:49.618 --> 06:51.662
You got her a guitar?

06:51.662 --> 06:54.456
Eh, this is for Bridget.

06:54.456 --> 06:57.627
There were no good rings.

06:57.627 --> 07:00.838
Come on, come on.
Let's go.

07:00.838 --> 07:02.548
[grunts]

07:04.424 --> 07:05.968
[exhales]

07:05.968 --> 07:07.761
[car engine turns over]

07:23.026 --> 07:24.570
[grunts]

07:26.446 --> 07:28.448
O'Connor's?

07:30.033 --> 07:33.663
[Avi] Look, when I was training
to be a soldier in Israel,

07:33.663 --> 07:36.164
they teach you one thing
above all else.

07:36.164 --> 07:38.208
Don't look back.

07:38.208 --> 07:41.003
I'm not a soldier, Avi.

07:41.003 --> 07:44.507
Don't kid yourself, Ray.
You're a soldier.

07:44.507 --> 07:49.554
♪♪♪

08:01.440 --> 08:02.816
[Sonia] Is that girl dead?

08:02.816 --> 08:05.611
Sonia, you're missing the point.

08:11.533 --> 08:13.410
He killed Ivan.

08:17.497 --> 08:18.874
Where did you get this?

08:18.874 --> 08:20.792
Had to take care of
an official at the port

08:20.792 --> 08:21.877
who wasn't friendly.

08:24.421 --> 08:27.675
You brought Ray Donovan
into this and he killed Ivan.

08:29.843 --> 08:33.096
- You're right, I did.
- Dmitri will kill us all.

08:33.096 --> 08:34.848
- He'll be reasonable.
- [Vlad] He's not forgiving.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.642
- [Vlad] You know this.
- He's my uncle.

08:36.642 --> 08:38.018
[Vlad] He killed your father.

08:38.018 --> 08:40.646
He will kill you
and then he will kill us.

08:40.646 --> 08:42.898
We're too valuable to him.

08:44.650 --> 08:47.945
- [computer beeps]
- So...

08:47.945 --> 08:50.656
...we wait.

08:50.656 --> 08:53.659
Yes.

08:53.659 --> 08:56.704
Go back to work.
I'll take care of this.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.214
What?

09:07.214 --> 09:10.050
Hey, um, this a bad time?

09:10.050 --> 09:12.762
What the fuck do you think?

09:12.762 --> 09:15.263
Look, Hector wanted me
to give this to you.

09:23.731 --> 09:26.608
Oh, what, am I his whore now?

09:26.608 --> 09:29.111
I don't know,
he just wants you to go away.

09:29.111 --> 09:30.320
Go away?

09:30.320 --> 09:32.322
With this?

09:35.534 --> 09:38.537
♪ dramatic music ♪

09:38.537 --> 09:43.542
♪♪♪

10:10.652 --> 10:12.863
[photographer] Boom!
One, two, boom.

10:12.863 --> 10:14.656
Boom, yeah.
Boom.

10:14.656 --> 10:16.241
Hit a combo, I'ma hit you.

10:16.241 --> 10:17.826
Bam!
Love these combos.

10:17.826 --> 10:18.869
Nice, champ.

10:18.869 --> 10:20.078
Lovin' it.
Lovin'.

10:20.078 --> 10:21.413
Okay, what I want you
to do now is,

10:21.413 --> 10:22.664
I want you to square up,

10:22.664 --> 10:24.667
cross your arms,
give me that attitude, okay?

10:24.667 --> 10:26.669
A'ight, that's easy.

10:26.669 --> 10:27.627
- [breathes deeply]
- [photographer] Nice.

10:27.627 --> 10:29.171
- Head up.
- [camera clicks]

10:29.171 --> 10:30.839
Beautiful.
Chin down.

10:30.839 --> 10:32.758
Got you in the background.
Beautiful.

10:32.758 --> 10:35.093
Punch, why don't you
get in the shot with your boy.

10:35.093 --> 10:36.679
[camera clicks]

10:36.679 --> 10:38.346
- [photographer] Nice, you guys.
- You too, Terry.

10:38.346 --> 10:40.223
No, you're good.

10:40.223 --> 10:41.684
[camera clicks]

10:41.684 --> 10:43.685
Come on.
Get your ass up here.

10:46.563 --> 10:48.733
- [Hector] Here he comes.
- [camera clicks]

10:48.733 --> 10:52.152
Welcome to the party, big guy.

10:52.152 --> 10:54.697
- [grunts]
- [photographer] Nice.

10:56.448 --> 10:57.657
Come on, brother.
Don't be shy.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.034
Slide in with your boys.

10:59.034 --> 11:01.161
[camera clicks]

11:01.161 --> 11:02.829
Part of Team Campos now, man.

11:04.874 --> 11:06.166
[photographer] Nice.

11:06.166 --> 11:07.793
We're doing,
uh, tough stuff here.

11:07.793 --> 11:09.127
I don't know if you heard.
No smiling.

11:09.127 --> 11:12.130
[camera clicking]

11:13.548 --> 11:18.553
♪♪♪

11:44.830 --> 11:46.123
What're we doing?

11:46.123 --> 11:47.791
Going to see a friend.

11:47.791 --> 11:49.876
But I have a history test.

11:49.876 --> 11:53.923
That's okay, darling.
You can take it tomorrow.

12:04.891 --> 12:07.894
[car door alarm chiming]

12:09.563 --> 12:11.356
Buckle up.

12:12.357 --> 12:13.900
[car engine turns over]

12:18.572 --> 12:21.575
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

12:21.575 --> 12:26.580
♪♪♪

12:49.895 --> 12:51.813
Shit.
Terry!

12:51.813 --> 12:53.815
Terry, there's a fire!

12:55.483 --> 12:57.652
Hurry up.

12:57.652 --> 12:59.779
[Daryll] Oh, shit!

12:59.779 --> 13:01.740
Sh--oh!

13:10.790 --> 13:13.585
- [lively music on TV]
- There it is.

13:13.585 --> 13:15.212
There she is.

13:17.589 --> 13:19.591
[phone rings]

13:21.092 --> 13:23.595
[phone beeps]

13:23.595 --> 13:25.931
- Hey, Bunch.
- [Bunchy] Hey, Abby.

13:25.931 --> 13:28.850
How are you?

13:28.850 --> 13:31.770
- How's Maria?
- [Abby] She's good.

13:31.770 --> 13:35.023
She just ate lunch,
and now she's watching TV.

13:35.023 --> 13:36.942
- [chuckles]
- [Bunchy] Oh, good.

13:36.942 --> 13:40.070
So, listen, we got Teresa,

13:40.070 --> 13:42.907
but we--we gotta make
a little pit stop.

13:42.907 --> 13:44.950
You think you could watch her
for one more day?

13:44.950 --> 13:47.410
Of course.

13:47.410 --> 13:49.621
No rush, Bunchy.

13:49.621 --> 13:51.916
[Bunchy] Hey, honey,

13:51.916 --> 13:54.167
you wanna talk to Maria?

13:54.167 --> 13:55.377
Hmm?

13:55.377 --> 13:57.629
Go ahead.
Talk to her.

13:57.629 --> 13:59.256
Say hi.

13:59.256 --> 14:02.175
[Maria babbles]

14:02.175 --> 14:04.177
Hi, baby.

14:05.262 --> 14:08.265
[coos]

14:08.265 --> 14:09.641
[Bunchy] Anyway, uh,

14:09.641 --> 14:11.977
thank you, Abby.

14:11.977 --> 14:13.937
We'll get her
out of your hair tomorrow.

14:13.937 --> 14:16.856
Let you get back to your life,
okay?

14:18.984 --> 14:20.986
Okay, bye, Bunch.

14:22.070 --> 14:23.780
[phone beeps]

14:23.780 --> 14:26.033
Your mama's comin' home.

14:28.576 --> 14:30.120
[doorbell rings]

14:31.746 --> 14:34.749
[lively music continues
on television]

14:34.749 --> 14:36.751
♪♪♪

14:36.751 --> 14:40.297
Ooh, go in here
for a little nap.

14:40.297 --> 14:41.423
There you go.

14:41.423 --> 14:42.841
I'll be right back.

14:42.841 --> 14:44.634
There you go.

14:51.976 --> 14:53.310
Can I help you?

14:53.310 --> 14:55.145
My name is Sonia Kovitzky.

14:55.145 --> 14:57.439
This is my daughter, Katya.

15:00.900 --> 15:03.111
[quietly]
What're you doing here?

15:03.111 --> 15:04.988
May we come in?

15:04.988 --> 15:06.406
No.

15:07.490 --> 15:09.743
Katya, put your music on.

15:13.663 --> 15:16.708
Your husband killed
an important man.

15:16.708 --> 15:19.627
Your family is in trouble
and so is mine.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.254
Now, please, may we come in?

15:21.254 --> 15:23.715
Jesus Christ.

15:23.715 --> 15:25.675
Just wait here.

15:27.052 --> 15:28.303
[sighs]

15:28.303 --> 15:29.554
[phone beeps]

15:30.973 --> 15:33.976
[phone dialing and ringing]

15:36.979 --> 15:38.938
That woman's here.

15:38.938 --> 15:40.732
She brought her fucking kid.

15:40.732 --> 15:42.609
- [inhales sharply]
- [Ray] I'm on my way.

15:43.902 --> 15:45.154
[phone beeps]

15:45.154 --> 15:48.157
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

15:48.157 --> 15:50.533
♪♪♪

15:50.533 --> 15:52.327
[Abby] Come in.

15:58.500 --> 16:01.503
♪ dramatic music ♪

16:01.503 --> 16:06.424
♪ ♪

16:31.991 --> 16:34.994
[phone buzzing]

16:44.629 --> 16:46.548
Where the fuck are we?

16:46.548 --> 16:50.177
We're where I'm gonna
get my money back.

16:50.177 --> 16:51.678
Look at this.

16:52.804 --> 16:55.807
What's in the bag?

16:55.807 --> 16:57.142
Plasma cutter.

16:57.142 --> 17:00.645
State of the art shit.
Look.

17:00.645 --> 17:02.188
I...

17:02.188 --> 17:05.150
...got this for you.
Here.

17:05.150 --> 17:07.026
[quietly]
What's the mat--

17:07.026 --> 17:08.570
Teresa's in the back seat.

17:08.570 --> 17:10.280
Yeah, she'll be fine.

17:10.280 --> 17:13.366
- This is a safe neighborhood.
- Goddamn it, Mickey.

17:13.366 --> 17:15.034
Look, it's all pre-arranged.

17:15.034 --> 17:18.371
All we gotta do is go in,
cut the safe, get the money.

17:18.371 --> 17:21.416
Gone in 15 minutes tops.

17:21.416 --> 17:23.252
Look, the money inside?

17:23.252 --> 17:24.461
Half of it is
yours and Teresa's.

17:24.461 --> 17:26.088
Two million dollars.

17:26.088 --> 17:28.215
We don't need money.

17:28.215 --> 17:29.966
[breathing heavily]
Yeah.

17:29.966 --> 17:33.761
Yeah, but--look,
I need your help.

17:33.761 --> 17:35.847
I wanna go back to Boston.

17:35.847 --> 17:37.474
Live out my final years
with Sylvie,

17:37.474 --> 17:39.851
but I can't do that
if I got nothin' to offer.

17:39.851 --> 17:41.603
Fuck.

17:41.603 --> 17:43.021
15 minutes?

17:43.021 --> 17:45.190
- Yeah, tops.
- [sighs]

17:48.610 --> 17:50.154
[exhales]

17:50.154 --> 17:53.157
♪ soft music ♪

17:53.157 --> 17:56.201
♪♪♪

17:56.201 --> 17:58.036
- Beautiful.
- Mickey.

17:58.036 --> 17:59.287
[laughs softly]

18:01.080 --> 18:04.584
Hey, baby.
Ooh.

18:04.584 --> 18:07.629
♪♪♪

18:07.629 --> 18:09.422
Come on, Mickey.

18:13.760 --> 18:15.262
[Mickey grunts]

18:23.311 --> 18:26.022
Safe is behind the buffalo head.

18:26.022 --> 18:29.817
Holy shit.
[laughs]

18:29.817 --> 18:32.070
Pretty sneaky, huh?

18:35.615 --> 18:38.618
Hey, pop, who's that?

18:38.618 --> 18:40.245
Ah, don't worry about her.

18:40.245 --> 18:41.955
She's a mute.

18:41.955 --> 18:45.292
May--maybe deaf too.

18:45.292 --> 18:47.544
Okay, go keep an eye out.

18:48.878 --> 18:50.129
Fifteen minutes.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.923
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

18:53.049 --> 18:54.551
Let's hit this.

18:58.305 --> 19:00.181
Push it.
[grunts and strains]

19:00.181 --> 19:02.226
Look, just--

19:02.226 --> 19:05.061
that was easy.
Over here.

19:05.061 --> 19:06.187
[grunts]

19:06.187 --> 19:07.480
[breathing heavily]

19:09.941 --> 19:12.236
There she is.

19:21.411 --> 19:24.414
[torch compressor hums]

19:28.876 --> 19:30.169
[Mickey exhales sharply]

19:33.881 --> 19:35.258
Wow.

19:36.259 --> 19:39.012
Watch the master work here.

19:40.972 --> 19:42.974
This is gonna cut like butter.

19:50.398 --> 19:53.610
[woman on radio] Engine 2711,
battalion eight.

19:53.610 --> 19:55.194
[unintelligible radio chatter]

19:55.194 --> 19:57.322
- Hi.
- Hi.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.117
Your sister-in-law
ever get her purse back?

20:01.117 --> 20:03.202
Oh, yeah.
Sh--she did.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.247
Thanks.

20:05.247 --> 20:07.374
So do you know this girl?

20:07.374 --> 20:09.251
Uh, she's my fighter's sister,

20:09.251 --> 20:11.628
an--and they di--

20:11.628 --> 20:12.754
well, they have--

20:12.754 --> 20:15.173
Yeah, I've seen the news.

20:15.173 --> 20:17.426
She gonna go to jail?

20:17.426 --> 20:19.386
She's gonna have to go
for a night or two, yeah.

20:19.386 --> 20:20.345
Ah.

20:20.345 --> 20:23.222
I-I feel kinda bad for her.

20:23.222 --> 20:26.435
Yeah, me too.

20:26.435 --> 20:29.438
[indistinct chatter]

20:30.271 --> 20:32.065
Okay, well,

20:32.065 --> 20:34.067
these guys should be out
of here before too long,

20:34.067 --> 20:36.110
um, and you're gonna need
a copy of the report

20:36.110 --> 20:37.321
for your insurance claim.

20:37.321 --> 20:39.322
Okay, thanks.

20:41.282 --> 20:44.328
- Uh, wait.
- Yeah?

20:47.747 --> 20:52.336
Do you have a boyfriend
or a husband or somethin'?

20:52.336 --> 20:55.338
- Why?
- Well, I thought maybe you--

20:55.338 --> 20:58.091
you'd like to have dinner
with me sometime.

21:01.177 --> 21:03.262
How 'bout a drink instead?

21:03.262 --> 21:05.431
Yeah, that's even better.

21:09.477 --> 21:11.729
You're looking well.

21:13.648 --> 21:17.235
What the hell does that mean?

21:17.235 --> 21:19.654
I know that you're
undergoing treatment.

21:22.449 --> 21:24.450
Is that so?

21:26.370 --> 21:30.289
I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to be indelicate.

21:32.166 --> 21:36.504
Talking about my cancer
isn't indelicate.

21:36.504 --> 21:39.674
Coming here
after you fucked my husband,

21:39.674 --> 21:41.676
that's indelicate.

21:41.676 --> 21:44.387
♪♪♪

21:44.387 --> 21:45.930
[sighs]

21:53.688 --> 21:56.315
Did your daughter like
the painting?

21:56.315 --> 22:00.695
She thought it was
very generous.

22:00.695 --> 22:04.699
I really was sorry
to hear about your diagnosis.

22:04.699 --> 22:06.951
Are you in love with him?

22:06.951 --> 22:08.119
[Sonia] No,

22:08.119 --> 22:10.497
and even if I was,

22:10.497 --> 22:13.750
I have late stage cancer.

22:13.750 --> 22:17.170
So you fucked my husband
because you're dying?

22:17.170 --> 22:18.504
[sighs]

22:18.504 --> 22:20.465
You're very blunt.

22:20.465 --> 22:22.717
Look, this...

22:22.717 --> 22:25.720
[sighs]

22:27.180 --> 22:29.558
This is not new for me,

22:29.558 --> 22:30.892
and you weren't new for him.

22:30.892 --> 22:32.436
Know that.

22:32.436 --> 22:35.480
Man has his own apartment
for fuck sakes.

22:37.524 --> 22:40.318
I know exactly where I am.

22:54.832 --> 22:56.460
[phone dialing and ringing]

22:56.460 --> 22:58.085
Sonia's at my house.

22:58.085 --> 23:00.379
[Avi] Fuck.

23:00.379 --> 23:03.132
[Ray]
She's got a guy parked outside.

23:03.132 --> 23:05.176
Ray, we're done here.

23:05.176 --> 23:07.512
A customs official was executed.

23:07.512 --> 23:09.096
Gates?

23:09.096 --> 23:11.015
[Avi]
No, the guy who runs security.

23:11.015 --> 23:11.808
[Ray] All right.

23:14.143 --> 23:17.146
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

23:17.146 --> 23:21.610
♪♪♪

23:21.610 --> 23:23.861
[door opens and closes]

23:26.239 --> 23:27.740
Fuck's going on here?

23:27.740 --> 23:30.535
I need to speak with you.

23:32.745 --> 23:34.831
Why is your boy parked outside?

23:34.831 --> 23:36.457
I didn't realize he was.

23:38.460 --> 23:40.211
Where are the kids?

23:40.211 --> 23:42.004
Conor's out.

23:42.004 --> 23:45.842
Bridget's upstairs in her room
with her daughter.

23:49.596 --> 23:51.848
Can I speak with you privately?

23:54.433 --> 23:56.435
Whatever you have to say,
say it.

23:58.647 --> 24:01.357
There's footage from the port
of the dead girl.

24:01.357 --> 24:04.443
Of Ivan going in
and not coming out.

24:04.443 --> 24:07.071
- You killed him.
- Yes.

24:07.071 --> 24:09.448
- [Sonia] After all of that?
- He murdered that girl.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.617
So you make it your business
to commit suicide

24:11.617 --> 24:13.578
and take me down with you?

24:13.578 --> 24:15.497
Anyone else see the footage?

24:15.497 --> 24:17.499
Vlad, Waller.

24:17.499 --> 24:18.749
What're they gonna do?

24:18.749 --> 24:20.585
My uncle's
en route from Moscow.

24:20.585 --> 24:22.587
He'll be at my gallery at 7:30.

24:22.587 --> 24:25.006
I tried to hire a plane
and get a passport,

24:25.006 --> 24:28.467
but Vlad, Waller, someone has
cut me off from my resources.

24:31.470 --> 24:32.930
I'll talk to him.

24:32.930 --> 24:34.265
[Sonia] They won't listen.

24:34.265 --> 24:35.474
Please.

24:35.474 --> 24:38.728
Please,
I have nowhere to turn.

24:38.728 --> 24:40.647
Help me and my daughter
disappear.

24:40.647 --> 24:42.690
Get rid of Vlad and Waller

24:42.690 --> 24:44.651
before my uncle finds out
what you did.

24:44.651 --> 24:45.943
Fuck no.

24:48.362 --> 24:50.823
[quietly]
Please?

24:50.823 --> 24:54.076
♪♪♪

24:54.076 --> 24:55.704
This is ridiculous.

24:55.704 --> 24:58.164
They shouldn't be
falling out like this.

24:58.164 --> 25:00.374
Trudy, she's a very nice girl,

25:00.374 --> 25:03.628
but she does not understand
white hair.

25:04.629 --> 25:06.255
There's a guy in Vegas,

25:06.255 --> 25:07.590
does excellent work.

25:07.590 --> 25:10.092
It's pricey, but it's worth it.

25:11.594 --> 25:13.596
Yeah, I'm almost there, baby.

25:14.597 --> 25:16.682
I'm almost there.

25:16.682 --> 25:19.685
[torch compressor humming]

25:20.728 --> 25:23.606
It's taking a long time, pop.

25:23.606 --> 25:26.693
It's almost there.

25:26.693 --> 25:28.653
[torch compressor stalls]

25:28.653 --> 25:30.321
Fuck.

25:30.321 --> 25:32.031
[Mickey] What the...

25:32.031 --> 25:34.033
...fuck.

25:37.119 --> 25:39.623
This piece of shit.

25:41.123 --> 25:43.542
Probably made in Rangoon
or some fuckin' place.

25:43.542 --> 25:45.503
All right, let's go.
Okay?

25:45.503 --> 25:47.505
You gave it a good try.

25:48.632 --> 25:50.634
No.

25:53.302 --> 25:55.721
Go keep an eye on the old lady.

25:55.721 --> 25:57.556
I'm not gonna go scare her.

25:57.556 --> 25:59.141
Just sit with her.

25:59.141 --> 26:01.978
Make sure the .9 mil is
in your lap, visible.

26:01.978 --> 26:04.271
You said 15 minutes.

26:04.271 --> 26:05.856
I'm not gonna go hurt nobody.

26:05.856 --> 26:08.777
No one's gettin' hurt.
Trust me.

26:08.777 --> 26:13.280
♪♪♪

26:13.280 --> 26:15.950
- [sighs]
- Hey.

26:15.950 --> 26:18.411
You're a good boy.

26:20.789 --> 26:22.707
Fuck you, Mick.

26:22.707 --> 26:25.710
♪ dramatic music ♪

26:25.710 --> 26:30.715
♪♪♪

26:32.591 --> 26:35.594
[Sylvie] Hold this
before I let you go downstairs.

26:35.594 --> 26:38.597
Top of the mornin', cocksucker.

26:46.731 --> 26:49.233
We leave the lady out of this,
eh?

26:49.233 --> 26:51.027
Come here, sweetie.

26:54.656 --> 26:56.991
Really?

26:56.991 --> 27:00.786
Algoma always warned me
not to live with show-women.

27:00.786 --> 27:04.415
Look, I need the combination
to the safe.

27:04.415 --> 27:05.708
The combination?

27:05.708 --> 27:07.877
I-I-I don't think I remember
the combination.

27:07.877 --> 27:09.628
I'm not playin'.

27:09.628 --> 27:11.756
[Mickey] You reported it
stolen, didn't you?

27:11.756 --> 27:13.674
And I'm sure you collected
on the insurance.

27:13.674 --> 27:16.302
You got your money, now...

27:16.302 --> 27:19.681
...I want mine.

27:19.681 --> 27:22.851
The combination is: 21,

27:22.851 --> 27:24.643
36,

27:24.643 --> 27:26.437
go fuck yourself.

27:27.689 --> 27:30.232
Go to your window.
What do you see?

27:33.652 --> 27:36.655
Now tell me what you see.

27:36.655 --> 27:37.948
That's my other son.

27:37.948 --> 27:39.950
He's got a screw loose.

27:39.950 --> 27:42.411
There's not telling
what he might do.

27:42.411 --> 27:43.996
[whimpering]

27:43.996 --> 27:46.290
M-m-m-mama!

27:46.290 --> 27:47.750
[muffled]
Mama!

27:49.251 --> 27:52.296
[breathing heavily]

27:54.131 --> 27:56.258
I'm not a very strong swimmer.
[chuckles]

27:56.258 --> 27:58.511
You know?
I mean, I could swim,

27:58.511 --> 28:01.680
play in the water, but...
[sighs]

28:01.680 --> 28:03.724
When I was little,

28:03.724 --> 28:05.894
my mother, she took
my brother Ray and me

28:05.894 --> 28:08.562
to this swim class at the Y.

28:08.562 --> 28:09.939
[exhales]

28:09.939 --> 28:11.690
First day there,

28:11.690 --> 28:13.192
this kid fell in, hit his head,

28:13.192 --> 28:15.861
almost died.

28:15.861 --> 28:18.447
Frickin' lifeguard
didn't even jump in to save him.

28:18.447 --> 28:21.700
You understand, Mr. Donovan,
I know everything about you.

28:21.700 --> 28:24.120
Where you live,
where you're from.

28:24.120 --> 28:26.330
You think I'm not prepared
for this sort of thing?

28:26.330 --> 28:27.873
He seemed prepared to you,
sweetie?

28:27.873 --> 28:30.209
- Hell, no.
- You don't seem prepared to me.

28:30.209 --> 28:31.335
Here, you fuck.

28:31.335 --> 28:34.756
Move.
Move, you fuck.

28:34.756 --> 28:37.466
They scooped him out with that--
that big hook.

28:37.466 --> 28:39.510
You know, the big blue hook.

28:39.510 --> 28:42.138
And there was all blood
in the water.

28:42.138 --> 28:45.808
Me and my brother,
we were really scared, right?

28:45.808 --> 28:47.852
So from then on, when we were
supposed to go to class,

28:47.852 --> 28:49.103
we--we'd skip it.

28:49.103 --> 28:50.521
We'd go to the park.

28:50.521 --> 28:51.939
We'd get our--our suit
and our hair wet

28:51.939 --> 28:54.733
in the drinking fountain.
Yeah.

28:58.779 --> 29:00.990
Anyway.

29:00.990 --> 29:03.701
I'm not a real strong swimmer.

29:05.202 --> 29:06.662
You?

29:06.662 --> 29:08.998
- You fuck, here.
- [grunts]

29:08.998 --> 29:11.917
You hurt that woman,
you destroy an entire ancestry.

29:11.917 --> 29:13.962
Good, then give me
the combination.

29:13.962 --> 29:15.254
[panting]

29:15.254 --> 29:17.506
My men'll hunt you down
and kill you.

29:17.506 --> 29:19.216
[Mickey] Your men ain't been
west of Primm.

29:19.216 --> 29:21.635
Yeah, try your luck.

29:21.635 --> 29:23.470
Give me the fuckin' combination.

29:23.470 --> 29:24.889
The combination is:

29:24.889 --> 29:28.350
one, two, fuck you.

29:28.350 --> 29:29.935
Hey!
[grunts]

29:29.935 --> 29:32.062
[grunting]

29:32.062 --> 29:34.106
- [straining]
- [grunts]

29:34.106 --> 29:37.484
[grunts]
What--you little fucker.

29:37.484 --> 29:39.111
How long for the passport?

29:39.111 --> 29:42.114
Ah, that's easy.
Shouldn't take long at all.

29:42.114 --> 29:44.909
- [Ray sighs]
- Look, let's kill her now,

29:44.909 --> 29:47.161
then kill him, and the lawyer.

29:47.161 --> 29:48.913
She has a kid.

29:48.913 --> 29:52.291
What about your kids, Ray?

29:52.291 --> 29:53.792
First thing we gotta do is
get her boy out

29:53.792 --> 29:57.171
from in front of my house.

29:57.171 --> 29:59.966
[Lena] Sonia and I are
the same size.

30:01.508 --> 30:03.636
- Similar cheekbones too.
- [Avi] Mm-hmm.

30:03.636 --> 30:05.471
No.

30:06.805 --> 30:08.892
Yeah.

30:08.892 --> 30:11.769
I put on her clothes,
I do my hair, I get in her car,

30:11.769 --> 30:14.271
that dickbag follows me, and
I'll take him somewhere quiet.

30:14.271 --> 30:16.273
And then what?

30:17.483 --> 30:20.444
You know what.

30:20.444 --> 30:23.864
You know, she actually does look
a lot like her.

30:23.864 --> 30:26.951
What if he gets the drop on you?

30:26.951 --> 30:28.953
He won't.

30:33.582 --> 30:36.585
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

30:36.585 --> 30:41.632
♪ ♪

31:03.654 --> 31:04.906
- [breathing shakily]
- You want him to shoot her?

31:04.906 --> 31:06.031
No, no.

31:06.031 --> 31:07.408
[Mickey] Bunch...

31:07.408 --> 31:08.993
Mickey!

31:08.993 --> 31:10.869
[gun cocks]

31:10.869 --> 31:12.037
Shoot him, Larry.

31:12.037 --> 31:14.039
Drop the gun, Chip!

31:14.039 --> 31:15.749
[Mickey] There's something in it
for you, Larry.

31:15.749 --> 31:17.293
[crying softly]

31:17.293 --> 31:20.088
Look, help me get the safe open,

31:20.088 --> 31:22.006
I'll cut you in, easy breezy.

31:22.006 --> 31:24.550
Algoma's outside
with a gun to her head.

31:24.550 --> 31:26.427
What do you want me to do, boss?

31:26.427 --> 31:30.056
Either you walk out of here
or Larry shoots your girl.

31:30.056 --> 31:31.932
- Fuck you.
- No, no, no.

31:31.932 --> 31:34.435
- [Little Bill] Do it! Do it!
- [Sylvie] Don't!

31:34.435 --> 31:36.520
Now drop the fucking gun!

31:36.520 --> 31:38.314
- Ah!
- [grunts]

31:40.524 --> 31:45.571
♪♪♪

31:51.285 --> 31:54.288
[breathing shakily]

32:08.677 --> 32:11.096
[gunshot]

32:11.096 --> 32:13.349
[gunshots]

32:13.349 --> 32:18.145
[whimpering and crying]
Jesus Christ.

32:18.145 --> 32:21.940
Jesus Christ.
Jesus Christ.

32:31.992 --> 32:35.621
6-26-76.

32:35.621 --> 32:38.540
Battle of the Little Big Horn.

32:46.049 --> 32:49.052
[whimpering and crying softly]

32:54.098 --> 32:55.641
I want you to call Margaret

32:55.641 --> 32:58.185
and tell her you're leaving
for Boston in the morning.

32:58.185 --> 32:59.603
The fuck I am.

32:59.603 --> 33:01.438
[sighs]

33:01.438 --> 33:03.066
You're taking our kids

33:03.066 --> 33:05.526
and you're going to stay
with your sister, Abby.

33:13.075 --> 33:16.703
You don't fuckin' get it,
do you?

33:16.703 --> 33:19.207
I killed someone.
Remember?

33:19.207 --> 33:21.959
I am not the fuckin'
little woman anymore, Ray.

33:21.959 --> 33:23.169
That part's over.

33:23.169 --> 33:24.420
I need to know
the kids are safe.

33:24.420 --> 33:27.173
They will be,

33:27.173 --> 33:29.258
but I am staying.

33:29.258 --> 33:31.052
[sighs]

33:32.761 --> 33:35.681
[Abby]
Listen to me.

33:35.681 --> 33:39.017
I am so fuckin' tired
of not being able to control

33:39.017 --> 33:42.188
what happens to me
with this fuckin' cancer.

33:42.188 --> 33:45.691
Or what happens to you
or what happens to this family.

33:45.691 --> 33:47.025
♪ soft music ♪

33:47.025 --> 33:48.902
Do you get that?

33:51.197 --> 33:52.448
[sighs]

33:58.287 --> 34:01.832
I'm not losing you, Abby.

34:01.832 --> 34:03.667
You won't,

34:03.667 --> 34:06.211
but I'm stayin'.

34:06.211 --> 34:10.048
♪♪♪

34:10.048 --> 34:12.676
All right.

34:12.676 --> 34:16.222
Call Deb,
see if she can take the kids.

34:19.600 --> 34:21.768
[Ray] You don't have to do this.

34:21.768 --> 34:23.770
It's gonna be fine, Ray.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.772
I'm sending Avi with you.

34:25.772 --> 34:27.649
Look, I know you wish Avi
could do everything,

34:27.649 --> 34:30.111
but you forget
who you're dealing with.

34:30.111 --> 34:31.320
[Lena] I'm gonna be fast.
I promise.

34:31.320 --> 34:33.113
It's gonna be fine.

34:33.113 --> 34:35.491
All right.

34:35.491 --> 34:38.660
You see anything off, anything,

34:38.660 --> 34:40.245
keep driving and call one of us.

34:40.245 --> 34:42.123
I promise.
Okay?

34:42.123 --> 34:45.125
Enough.
I will call you when I'm done.

34:48.962 --> 34:50.923
She can do it.
No problem.

34:50.923 --> 34:52.549
You don't know her like I do.

34:52.549 --> 34:54.301
It's not right.

34:54.301 --> 34:56.637
[Avi] It's the only way, Ray.

34:56.637 --> 35:00.057
Sh--she's tougher
than the both of us.

35:01.058 --> 35:02.559
Listen.

35:02.559 --> 35:05.270
You have to kill that woman.

35:05.270 --> 35:06.939
Just take care of the lawyer.

35:06.939 --> 35:09.691
Listen, if you don't trust her,
you have to do it.

35:17.658 --> 35:19.076
[car engine turns over]

35:19.076 --> 35:21.870
[car engine turns over]

35:44.352 --> 35:46.353
Pop.

35:48.480 --> 35:51.234
You guys wait outside.

35:54.486 --> 35:56.697
All right.

35:56.697 --> 36:00.201
Thank you, son.

36:00.201 --> 36:05.122
♪♪♪

36:17.718 --> 36:19.469
[sighs]

36:19.469 --> 36:23.515
I had mercy on you and your boy.
[crying]

36:26.935 --> 36:28.562
You did.

36:28.562 --> 36:31.607
Out on the highway, I...

36:31.607 --> 36:34.235
...I let you go.

36:34.235 --> 36:37.279
I coulda put a bullet
in both your heads.

36:37.279 --> 36:39.281
You shoulda.

36:50.083 --> 36:53.879
Don't kill Algoma.

36:53.879 --> 36:55.381
She's simple.

36:55.381 --> 36:57.758
She doesn't know
what's goin' on.

36:59.468 --> 37:01.261
Sure.

37:04.389 --> 37:05.932
[exhales]

37:07.309 --> 37:09.353
All right,
I'll be back in a couple hours.

37:09.353 --> 37:12.398
Okay.

37:12.398 --> 37:15.359
You're not gonna kill her,
are you?

37:15.359 --> 37:17.027
No.

37:17.027 --> 37:19.071
Even if you should?

37:21.990 --> 37:24.993
- If she fucks you over--
- She might.

37:28.622 --> 37:31.166
What do you want, Abby?

37:35.253 --> 37:37.298
I don't fuckin' know anymore,
Ray.

37:37.298 --> 37:39.300
[breathes heavily]

37:39.300 --> 37:44.305
♪♪♪

38:01.029 --> 38:02.656
May I?

38:02.656 --> 38:05.493
Sure.

38:05.493 --> 38:06.326
[Helen Reddy's Delta Dawn
plays on radio]

38:06.326 --> 38:08.245
Hmm.
[chuckles softly]

38:08.245 --> 38:10.372
♪ What's that flower
you have on?... ♪

38:10.372 --> 38:12.541
Do you remember
the battle of the sexes?

38:12.541 --> 38:15.377
♪ ...faded rose
from days gone by?... ♪

38:15.377 --> 38:16.878
Tennis?

38:16.878 --> 38:18.422
Yeah.

38:18.422 --> 38:19.965
This song

38:19.965 --> 38:22.468
was huge in '74.

38:22.468 --> 38:24.470
Bobby Riggs
and Billie Jean King?

38:24.470 --> 38:26.847
[chuckles softly]
Yes.

38:26.847 --> 38:30.517
That was 1973.

38:30.517 --> 38:34.396
My father threw his low-ball,
Scotch and all,

38:34.396 --> 38:37.441
right across the room
after that match.

38:37.441 --> 38:40.318
He had a huge wager on it.

38:40.318 --> 38:43.071
I was four years old
and I remember

38:43.071 --> 38:44.823
being in our great room,

38:44.823 --> 38:46.158
and my father saying to me

38:46.158 --> 38:49.953
that no woman
could ever beat a man,

38:49.953 --> 38:52.456
not in a game
of strength and strategy.

38:52.456 --> 38:54.166
♪♪♪

38:54.166 --> 38:57.252
- There was a lot of laughing.
- ♪ Delta Dawn... ♪

38:57.252 --> 38:59.796
Until there wasn't.

38:59.796 --> 39:02.340
She beat him.

39:02.340 --> 39:05.719
Annihilated him.

39:05.719 --> 39:08.722
And my father and my uncle
and all those men,

39:08.722 --> 39:11.057
they were so furious

39:11.057 --> 39:13.935
that this woman
had lost him all that money.

39:13.935 --> 39:15.729
♪ Mansion in the sky... ♪

39:15.729 --> 39:18.899
He was beside himself.

39:18.899 --> 39:20.859
You remember all that
from four years old?

39:20.859 --> 39:23.695
♪ What's that flower
you have on?... ♪

39:23.695 --> 39:25.447
♪ Could it be a faded... ♪

39:25.447 --> 39:27.699
I remember everything.

39:27.699 --> 39:30.076
Don't you?

39:30.076 --> 39:32.245
♪ And did I hear you say... ♪

39:32.245 --> 39:33.955
No.

39:33.955 --> 39:36.584
♪♪♪

39:36.584 --> 39:41.547
♪ To take you to his mansion
in the sky ♪

39:42.548 --> 39:45.551
[tires squealing]

39:50.431 --> 39:53.434
♪ soft dramatic music ♪

39:53.434 --> 39:58.439
♪♪♪

40:29.761 --> 40:32.222
Sonia, this is not--

40:33.431 --> 40:34.683
[elevator bell dings]

40:40.605 --> 40:45.610
♪♪♪

40:49.447 --> 40:50.699
[lock clicks]

41:01.710 --> 41:04.254
[quietly]
Hey, on your knees.

41:04.254 --> 41:05.422
[forceful whisper]
Now!

41:05.422 --> 41:07.966
- [scoffs]
- Get.

41:16.684 --> 41:19.562
Okay, okay, okay.

41:19.562 --> 41:21.104
Okay.

41:23.273 --> 41:25.525
[all grunting]

41:26.526 --> 41:27.819
Ah.

41:54.721 --> 41:58.099
Why are you doing this?

41:58.099 --> 41:59.727
Why am I doin' what?

41:59.727 --> 42:01.436
Helping me.

42:04.272 --> 42:06.816
I killed your man.

42:08.526 --> 42:10.862
Put you in a bad position.

42:10.862 --> 42:12.656
Still.

42:12.656 --> 42:15.659
It would have been easier
to just kill me.

42:16.826 --> 42:18.662
No, it wouldn't.

42:22.374 --> 42:26.086
If it comes down to it,
don't deal with Dmitri.

42:26.086 --> 42:27.545
Disappear.

42:27.545 --> 42:30.090
Or he'll kill you.

42:30.090 --> 42:31.925
Take care of yourself.

42:56.659 --> 42:58.661
You can keep the money.

42:58.661 --> 43:00.745
I don't want it no more.

43:00.745 --> 43:03.707
- Pop.
- I don't want it.

43:03.707 --> 43:06.501
I don't want nothin'.

43:07.669 --> 43:11.006
I thought...

43:11.006 --> 43:14.009
I thought I was gonna have
a new life.

43:19.014 --> 43:21.808
I thought...

43:29.733 --> 43:32.485
I'm really sorry.

43:38.366 --> 43:40.869
You're a good girl.

44:06.603 --> 44:09.606
[phone ringing]

44:11.692 --> 44:13.151
[phone beeps]

44:13.151 --> 44:15.153
- Yeah?
- [Avi] [coughs]

44:15.153 --> 44:18.156
[crying]

44:20.784 --> 44:22.243
I'm--

44:22.243 --> 44:24.037
I'm sorry, Ray.

44:24.037 --> 44:25.622
Avi?

44:25.622 --> 44:27.499
[Dmitri] Mr. Donovan,

44:27.499 --> 44:30.668
bring me my niece

44:30.668 --> 44:32.587
or I kill your Jew.

44:32.587 --> 44:35.632
[coughing]

44:40.678 --> 44:43.223
- [phone beeps]
- Avi?

44:45.683 --> 44:48.686
[jet engine rumbling]

44:50.773 --> 44:55.778
♪♪♪

45:25.766 --> 45:30.771
♪♪♪

